Problem.Description: JB is very fat . So he wants to Climb the stairs to reduce weight . One day , he finally reached the top of the stairs .Something strange has happened , The height of each floor of the stairs is starting to change . a[i] express the i-th?floor’s height after the change .There are n floors and he can start at arbitrary floor.The number of floors he had walked is equal to the value of happy. Your goal is to calculate the maximum value of happy . For example n=4 , a[1] =5, a[2] = 5 ,a[3]=4 , a[4]=2 , the maximum value of happy is 3 . JB can’t reach x-th floor from y-th floor when a[y]≤a[x] or x≤y.
Problem.InputSpec: The first line is an integer n (1≤n≤20000)indicating the number of floor . The following line contains n integer a[1],a[2],a[3] , ...... , a[n].
Problem.OutputSpec: For each test , output one integer indicating the maximum value of happy .
